\ Problem 3
\ Now create a word named \STARS which will print a skewed array of stars
\ (a rhomboid), given the height on the stack. Use a DO loop, and, for 
\ simplicity, make the width a constant ten stars.

s" stars.fs" included 

: indent ( n --) \ print n spaces
	spaces ;

: row ( --)
	10 stars ;

: \stars ( height --)
	0 do
		dup indent row cr
	loop drop ;

3 \stars
